<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06074144 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06074144 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  FREMONT; POLICE; PROBE; AUTO; ROBBERY; MULTIPLE; JUVENILE; SUSPECT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Three teen-agers suspected of stealing stereos from nearly 75 cars in the pastsix weeks were arrested by Fremont police early Wednesday.;    The arrestscame after the resident of an apartment complex on Tamayo Street saw two ofthe teen-agers peering into cars with flashlights and prying open the doorsaround 2 a.m. The resident called police, who cordoned off the complex andstopped the suspects' car as it tried to leave. Police found a number of carstereos in the car.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  3 TEENS HELD IN CAR-THEFT SPREE OF FREMONTCAR STEREO THEFTS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Police arrested Steven Cho, 18, of Fremont, one 17-year-old from Alamedaand one 16-year-old from Alameda.;    Police said the teen-agers admitted thatthey had burglarized 24 automobiles Wednesday and admitted being involvedindividually in as many as 50 other car stereo thefts since Feb. 5.;    Thethree teen-agers were arrested on suspicion of auto burglary, possession ofstolen property, conspiracy and petty theft, Fremont police said. Cho is beingheld on $185,000 bail in the Fremont Detention Facility, and the other two arein custody in juvenile hall.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Alameda County/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910314  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  178  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday March 14, 199100074144,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>